<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="direct-v">direct <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /də'rekt;dɪ'rekt;daɪ'rekt/    美 /də'rekt;dɪ'rekt;daɪ'rekt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>给…指路；指引：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you <strong>direct</strong> me <strong>to</strong> the station? 
你能告诉我车站怎么走吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>导演；指挥：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She prefers to act rather than direct. 
她宁愿当演员，不愿当导演。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>指导；负责；管理</strong></h4>
<p>to control or be in charge of sb / sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A new manager has been appointed to direct the project. 
派来一名新经理来负责这个项目。</p></div>

<h4 id="4order">4.<strong>命令(order)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police officers had been directed to search the building. 
警察奉命搜查大楼。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>对准某一目标 (方向)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I want to <strong>direct</strong> my efforts more <strong>towards</strong> my own projects.
我想把精力更多地投入到自己的项目中去。</p></div></div>